#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Secure boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: meta
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable and configure secure boot on IBM Z systems for new or updated "
"installations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the secure boot functionality to work on an &zseries; system, the "
"following conditions must be met."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The machine must be z15 T01, z15 T02, LinuxONE III LT1, LinuxONE III LT2, or "
"a later model."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable secure boot on LPAR where Linux is installed. This system can serve "
"as a &kvm; hypervisor. However, &kvm; virtual machines cannot have the "
"secure boot enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "You must use SCSI (FCP) disks (secure boot is not supported on DASD)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hardware migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you migrate to a different machine (for example, from z13 to z15), "
"ensure that the LPAR on the target machine has the secure boot state of the "
"system on its disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Changing the secure boot state must be performed according to the following "
"procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing secure boot state"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a new installation, add the attribute <literal>SUSE_SECURE_BOOT=1</"
"literal> to <filename>/etc/default/grub</filename> . If you are performing "
"an update, add <literal>SUSE_SECURE_BOOT=auto</literal> instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Call the <command>grub2-install</command> command to regenerate grub "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shut down the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change the configuration of the LPAR (enable or disable secure boot)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Secure boot on HMC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_secure_boot.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system on the disk configured with the <literal>secure=1</literal> "
"parameter can be booted on z15 HMC as long as the firmware supports the new "
"on-disk format (which is always the case on z15)."
msgstr ""
